      <lg type="edition">
<l>oṇpoṟic cēva leṭuppa vēṟṟeḻuntu</l>
<l>taṇpaṉi yuṟaikkum pularā ñāṅkar</l>
<l>nuṇkōṟ ciṟukiṇai cilampa voṟṟi</l>
<l>neṭuṅkaṭai niṉṟu pakaṭupala vāḻttit</l>
<l>taṉpuka ḻēttiṉe ṉāka vūṉpulan</l>
<l>taruṅkaṭi viyaṉakark kuṟukal vēṇṭik</l>
<l>kūmpuviṭu meṉpiṇi yaviḻtta vāmpaṟ</l>
<l>ṟēmpā †yuḷḷa taṅkamaḻ maṭaruḷap†</l>
<l>pāmpuri yaṉṉa vaṭiviṉa kāmpiṉ</l>
<l>kaḻaipaṭu coliyi ṉiḻaiyaṇi vārā</l>
<l>voṇpūṅ kaliṅka muṭīi nuṇpūṇ</l>
<l>vacintuvāṅku nucuppi ṉavvāṅ kuntik</l>
<l>kaṟpuṭai maṭantai taṟpuṟam pulla</l>
<l>veṟpeyarnta nōkki..............................</l>
<l>..............................................kaṟkoṇ</l>
<l>ṭaḻittup piṟantaṉe ṉāki yavvaḻip</l>
<l>piṟar, pāṭupukaḻ pāṭip paṭarpaṟi yēṉē</l>
<l>kuṟumulaik kalamarum pālār veṇmaṟi</l>
<l>naraimuka vūkamō ṭukaḷuñceṉa...............</l>
<l>..........................kaṉṟupala keḻīiya</l>
<l>kāṉkeḻu nāṭaṉ kaṭuntē raviyaṉeṉa</l>
<l>voruvaṉai yuṭaiyēṉ maṉṉē yāṉē</l>
<l>yaṟāṉevaṉ parikō veḷḷiyatu nilaiyē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>When I, having gotten up, as a bright-spotted cockerel aroused [me], (1)</l>
<l>at the time before dawn when cool dew drips, (2)</l>
<l>pressing [my] little Kiṇai drum with fine sticks so that it sounded, (3)</l>
<l>standing at the tall gate, praising bulls many (4)</l>
<l>as one who praised his fame, craving for meat, (5)</l>
<l>wanted to come near the heavily protected wide mansion, (6)</l>
<l>he put [on me] a bright flowered Kaliṅkam cloth (11a-d)</l>
<l>that would not come to be adorned by jewels of bamboo-strip fallen from bamboo (10)</l>
<l>with shafts that are shapely like the skin of a snake, (9)</l>
<l>???????????? flowing with the honey (8)</l>
<l>of white waterlilies that opened [their] soft outer petals, releasing the buds, (7)</l>
<l>[and], while a chaste woman embraced his back, (13) </l>
<l>with a pretty curved navel [and] very curved waist with fine ornaments (11df.) </l>
<l>looked at my movements(?) ………. (14)</l>
<l>………………………….. taking a stone (15)</l>
<l>[and] destroying?, being one who is born [again], that way (16)</l>
<l>I don’t know of setting out, singing the praise that sings others. (17)</l>
<l>A white kid becoming full of the milk that shoots from the short teat, (18)</l>
<l>that frolics along with the grey-faced black monkey….. (19)</l>
<l>………………. united with many calves, (20)</l>
<l>Indeed I have somebody, (22)</l>
<l>namely Aviyaṉ with a fact chariot, man from a forested land. (21)</l>
<l>He won’t cease [supporting me]. What distress do I have, in [this] position of Venus? (23)  </l>
</lg>
